reviewText: I gotta say I wasn't expecting the insane amount of extra material that comes in this little box! There's already the free comic and plush Red Fraggle, but every dvd has tons of behind the scenes and documentaries about Fraggle and Jim Henson Studio's! So much to watch for Kids AND adults alike!

I bought Fraggle Rock for my grandkids.  I was surprised when my daughter-in-law knew about the Fraggles.  She was so happy.  Hopefully, the children will love it as much as I did when watching it with my children.  Now my children can watch it with my grandkids.

I loved so did my son i took him back to when he was a child and me too i love watching it and he is just so happy next year i would like to get it for my daughter she grew up with it too !! thank you so much LindaNelson

most of the tv show they make for children these days are nothing but trash with now kind of mental, cultural, or spiritual value.  as a child this was a show that i truly loved and one that sparked my sisters and my imagination i such a positive way.  so glad to have this great series to do the same for my children, neices, and nephews.

Loved the show growing up and thought the box set was full of collectors items! Love the Red Fraggle stuffie and adore the comic inside. It has artists that worked on the recent graphic novel series from Archaia, so it was extra cool. I'm going to bring it to comic con and get it signed!
My 3 year old grandson and his father are definitely having a bonding moment watching this.  I remember watching this with my son the first time around.

Who (from my generation) doesn't love the Jim Henson creations?  This DVD set is a great addition to my Muppets collection!

The DVD set is broken into four seasons, yet if you go to the Muppet Wiki site there are actually 5 "seasons".  Just to let you know of you care about that sort of thing.
I use to watch the Fraggles when it use to come on TV with the Muppets. Love them.

I've been considering buying fraggle rock on digital and am glad I waited because I got this on lightning deal and it saved money and I got the great package with all the extras. Great show and great packaging. Highly recommend to anyone who loves jim henson.

I love Fraggle Rock! It is so amazing to have all of the episodes together. The only problem is it is not formatted for a wide screen. That means your have the black strips on either side of the show...no big deal except my husband says it will burn out the pixels and ruin the tv if you watch too much tv like that? Also its a show from the 80s...so the quality isn't that great haha!

One of my favorite shows growing up. This box set includes all 4 seasons, and each season includes a disc with bonus content. The plush Red key chain is nothing special, but it's nice that they included it. I mostly like that all the seasons are packaged together in this wonderfully designed box. I would definitely recommend this box set to anyone.

Great collection! I loved Fraggle Rock as a kid and now my kids can enjoy them too! However, the box set was missing the graphic novel. The box itself said it was included inside, I opened the box and there was no graphic novel and there was obviously extra space in the box set where the graphic novel was supposed to be. The plush keychain and all DVDs were inside just not the graphic novel. Great collection, I just want everything I paid for...

Kids thrilled to get this! It has all the seasons of the show, and it is the regular show, NOT the animated cartoon. I wanted to clarify that because the Amazon editorial description calls it "animated" and that made me a bit worried before I bought it. But it's the original! And the bonus material is awesome. A good buy all around if you love fraggles!

I came into the series a little late I mean really late. I saw the fraggles when they made an appearance on the Muppet Christmas special and I never got to watch them as a kid. When the series appeared on Hulu I marathoned through the whole thing. I've been a fan ever since. When I saw this box set I didn't hesitate to buy it. Great extras and archival footage included. The reason I gave it four stars is because they cut off Gerry Parks' interview. The feature ends abruptly. So sad. :(
